  "texts": [
    "Beyond circularity, confirming in silico whether a sequence represents a plasmid is a remarkable challenge.",
    "Although single-copy core genes have been used to assess the completeness of non-plasmid and non-viral genomes assembled from metagenomes 13, our understanding of the canonical features of plasmids is limited to a relatively small set of well-studied genes that are primarily derived from plasmids of model organisms in culture 24, 25.",
    "For instance, MOB-suite 25 identified canonical features for plasmid replication and conjugation in only 61% of the reference plasmid subtypes we used to train PlasX, which reveals the limits of conventional approaches to identify plasmid features and survey previously undescribed plasmids (Supplementary Table 1).",
    "Indeed, MOB-suite identified canonical features in only 10.1% of our predictions (Supplementary Table 8).",
    "Given this narrow sensitivity, we developed orthogonal data-driven strategies to increase confidence in our predictions (Supplementary Information)."
  ],
